uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.forms.inputs

Class CheckBoxInput

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.forms.inputs.CheckBoxInput
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BinaryInput<java.lang.String>, Input<java.lang.String>, ParseInput<java.lang.String>

    public class CheckBoxInput
extends java.lang.Object
implements ParseInput<java.lang.String>, BinaryInput<java.lang.String>
    A checkbox input. One peculiarity of Checkbox input is that it always has a valid state. Inserting an invalid input results in an unchecked state.

    spb
